From a7bd7ef85c69adfe8586f14a231d45a8fe9710f1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 6 Jun 2025 09:22:42 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 01/10] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Add 6 GHz power mode
 channels support

Currently, the hostapd parses and stores the 6 GHz band channels
received as part of NL80211_CMD_GET_WIPHY.
There are 9 different power modes in the 6 GHz band (3 AP power modes
and 6 Client power modes). The hostapd does not parse the
power mode specific channels. The channel data currently parsed
by hostapd is power mode independent and hence will not be
sufficient to get the exact capabilities of the 6 GHz band
channels for each power mode.

To fix this, add logic to parse and store the power mode specific
channel information sent as part of NL80211_CMD_GET_WIPHY.
This will allow hostapd to get the exact capabilities of the
6 GHz band channels for each power mode.

Introduce a new structure within the hostapd_hw_modes to hold the
6 GHz power mode specific channel list information. This structure
is valid only if the mode is 6 GHz.

Introduce new channel flag 'HOSTAPD_CHAN_PSD' which indicates PSD
support for the channel.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency:
n00-001-hostapd-add-support-for-6GHz-operation.patch
r32-001-hostapd-Add-support-to-receive-AFC-power-update-comp.patch

Signed-off-by: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
